adcrumb-sep">/</span><span class="breadcrumb-leaf">Human Resources</span></div></div></div></div></div><main id="main" role="main" class="clearfix " style=""><div class="fusion-row" style=""><section id="content" style="float: right;"><div id="post-481" class="post-481 page type-page status-publish hentry"> <span class="entry-title rich-snippet-hidden">Human Resources</span><span class="vcard rich-snippet-hidden"><span class="fn"><a href="https://peoria.medicine.uic.edu/author/demcdowe/" title="Posts by Drew" rel="author">Drew</a></span></span><span class="updated rich-snippet-hidden">2018-10-24T16:13:20+00:00</span><div class="post-content"><div class="fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling"  style='background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0);background-position: center center;background-repeat: no-repeat;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;'><div class="fusion-builder-row fusion-row "><div  class="fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion_builder_column_3_4  fusion-three-fourth fusion-column-first 3_4"  style='margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:20px;width:75%;width:calc(75% - ( ( 4% ) * 0.75 ) );margin-right: 4%;'><div class="fusion-column-wrapper" style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px;background-position:left top;background-repeat:no-repeat;-webkit-background-size:cover;-moz-background-size:cover;-o-background-size:cover;background-size:cover;"  data-bg-url=""><div class="fusion-text"><h1>Human Resources</h1><p>The Human Resources department at University of Illinois College of Medicine at Peoria oversees the employment process for civil service employment. We also provide a variety of services to employees in areas such as benefits, payroll, policy administration, and training.</p></div><div class="fusion-text"><h2>Useful Tools, Forms and Policies</h2></div><style type="text/css" scoped="scoped">.fusion-accordian #accordion-481-1 .panel-title a .fa-fusion-box{color:#fff}.fusion-accordian #accordion-481-1 .panel-title a .fa-fusion-box:before{font-size:13px;width:13px}.fusion-accordian #accordion-481-1 .panel-title a{font-size:1em}.fusion-accordian #accordion-481-1 .fa-fusion-box{background-color:#333;border-color:#333}.fusion-accordian #accordion-481-1 .panel-title a:hover,#accordion-481-1 .fusion-toggle-boxed-mode:hover .panel-title a{color:#63698e}.fusion-accordian #accordion-481-1 .panel-title .active .fa-fusion-box,.fusion-accordian #accordion-481-1 .panel-title a:hover .fa-fusion-box{background-color:#63698e!important;border-color:#63698e!important}</style><div class="accordian fusion-accordian"><div class="panel-group" id="accordion-481-1"><div class="fusion-panel panel-default"><div class="panel-heading"><h4 class="panel-title toggle"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-481-1" data-target="#84cd8c2a57df4642f" href="#84cd8c2a57df4642f"><div class="fusion-toggle-icon-wrapper"><i class="fa-fusion-box"></i></div><div class="fusion-toggle-heading">Pay</div></a></h4></div><div id="84cd8c2a57df4642f" class="panel-collapse collapse "><div class="panel-body toggle-content fusion-clearfix"><p><a href="https://nessie.uihr.uillinois.edu/cf/comp/index.cfm" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">NESSIE</a> — earnings statement, tax statement and direct deposit information</p><p><strong>Payroll Schedules:</strong></p><ul><li><a href="http://peoria.medicine.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/8/2017/02/2018-BW-PaySchedule.pdf" target="">2018 Bi-weekly Pay Schedule</a></li><li><a href="http://peoria.medicine.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/8/2017/02/2018-Monthly-Pay-Schedule.pdf" target="">2018 Monthly Pay Schedule</a></li><li><a href="http://peoria.medicine.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/8/2018/09/2019-BW-PaySchedule.pdf" target="">2019 Bi-weekly Pay Schedule</a></li><li><a href="http://peoria.medicine.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/8/2018/09/2019-Monthly-Pay-Schedule.pdf" target="">2019 Monthly Pay Schedule</a></li></ul></div></div></div><div class="fusion-panel panel-default"><div class="panel-heading"><h4 class="panel-title toggle"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-481-1" data-target="#f68cb073c29f71d35" href="#f68cb073c29f71d35"><div class="fusion-toggle-icon-wrapper"><i class="fa-fusion-box"></i></div><div class="fusion-toggle-heading">Time and Leave</div></a></h4></div><div id="f68cb073c29f71d35" class="panel-collapse collapse "><div class="panel-body toggle-content fusion-clearfix"><a href="https://eas.admin.uillinois.edu/eas/servlet/EasLogin?redirect=https://webprod.admin.uillinois.edu/ssa/servlet/SelfServiceLogin?appName=edu.uillinois.aits.SelfServiceLogin&amp;dad=BANPROD2" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Timesheet</a></p><p><a href="http://peoria.medicine.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/8/2017/02/Non-Exempt-Timesheet.pdf" target="">Non-exempt Timesheet</a> (PDF)</p><p><a href="https://hrnet.uihr.uillinois.edu/ptrapplication" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Positive Time Reporting</a><br /> &#8211; <a href="https://www.hr.uic.edu/uic101/positive_time/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Information on Positive Time Reporting</a></p><p><a href="http://peoria.medicine.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/8/2017/02/Request-for-Leave.pdf" target="">Request For Leave</a></p><p><a href="https://www.hr.uillinois.edu/cms/One.aspx?portalId=4292&amp;pageId=5624" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Holidays</a></div></div></div><div class="fusion-panel panel-default"><div class="panel-heading"><h4 class="panel-title toggle"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-481-1" data-target="#e1d25c3ca2b30f155" href="#e1d25c3ca2b30f155"><div class="fusion-toggle-icon-wrapper"><i class="fa-fusion-box"></i></div><div class="fusion-toggle-heading">Benefits</div></a></h4></div><div id="e1d25c3ca2b30f155" class="panel-collapse collapse "><div class="panel-body toggle-content fusion-clearfix"><a href="https://mybenefits.illinois.gov/">MyBenefits</a> — the state’s new online system for enrollment and changes to health, dental, life insurance, and flexible spending account plans</p><p><a href="https://www.hr.uillinois.edu/benefits/mybenefits_faq" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Frequently Asked Questions</a></p><p><a href="https://nessie.uihr.uillinois.edu/cf/events/index.cfm" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Life Events</a> — information on making changes to your benefits or personal information</p><p><a href="https://nessie.uihr.uillinois.edu/cf/index.cfm">NESSIE</a></p><p><a href="https://nessie.uihr.uillinois.edu/cf/events/index.cfm?Item_ID=1121&amp;rlink=1116">Tuition Waiver Form</a></div></div></div><div class="fusion-panel panel-default"><div class="panel-heading"><h4 class="panel-title toggle"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-481-1" data-target="#ef9bbd9dc7b45d5f6" href="#ef9bbd9dc7b45d5f6"><div class="fusion-toggle-icon-wrapper"><i class="fa-fusion-box"></i></div><div class="fusion-toggle-heading">Employment</div></a></h4></div><div id="ef9bbd9dc7b45d5f6" class="panel-collapse collapse "><div class="panel-body toggle-content fusion-clearfix"><h3>Employment Opportunity</h3><p>The University of Illinois College of Medicine Peoria has a full-time office support specialist position available in the Health Sciences Education Dept. This position will provide clerical support to the department: assist with curriculum materials, coordinate schedules and type correspondence.</p><p>The civil service minimum qualifications for the position may be found at: <a href="http://www.sucss.illinois.gov/specs/detail.aspx?ID=2810&amp;osm=c19" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">http://www.sucss.illinois.gov/specs/detail.aspx?ID=2810&amp;osm=c19</a>. A civil service exam will be administered to qualified candidates.</p><p>Please e-mail Human Resources at <a href="mailto:sdoerr@uic.edu">sdoerr@uic.edu</a> to request application instructions. Application deadline is January 18, 2018.</p><p>UICOMP is an EOE/AA/M/F/Disabled/Veteran. The University of IL may conduct background checks on all job candidates upon acceptance of a contingent offer. Background checks will be performed in compliance with the Fair Credit Report Act.</p><hr class="newhr" /><p><strong><a href="https://jobs.uic.edu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">jobs.uic.edu</a> — employment website</strong></p><p><a href="http://peoria.medicine.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/8/2017/02/Peoria-Online-Application-Instructions.pdf" target="">Application Instructions</a></p><p><a href="http://www.sucss.illinois.gov/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">State Universities Civil Service System (SUCSS)</a> — Civil Service Exam information, interview tips and more</p><p><a href="https://nessie.uihr.uillinois.edu/cf/index.cfm?Item_id=1076&amp;rlink=1974">Employment Verification</a></p><p><a href="https://www.hr.uic.edu/labor_relations/labor_agreements/">Union Contracts</a></p><p><em><strong><a href="http://policies.uic.edu/uic-policy-library/access-and-equity/nondiscrimination-policy-statement/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Nondiscrimination Statement</a></strong>: The University will not engage in discrimination or harassment against any person because of race, color, religion, sex, national origin, ancestry, age, order of protection status, genetic information, marital status, disability, sexual orientation including gender identity, unfavorable discharge from the military or status as a protected veteran and will comply with all federal and state nondiscrimination, equal opportunity and affirmative action laws, orders and regulations. This nondiscrimination policy applies to admissions, employment, access to and treatment in the University’s programs and activities.</em></p></div></div></div><div class="fusion-panel panel-default"><div class="panel-heading"><h4 class="panel-title toggle"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-481-1" data-target="#475f8094f14eaacc8" href="#475f8094f14eaacc8"><div class="fusion-toggle-icon-wrapper"><i class="fa-fusion-box"></i></div><div class="fusion-toggle-heading">Retirement</div></a></h4></div><div id="475f8094f14eaacc8" class="panel-collapse collapse "><div class="panel-body toggle-content fusion-clearfix"><a href="http://www.surs.org/">SURS (State Universities Retirement System)</a> — The University of Illinois offers a comprehensive retirement package. This includes participation in the State Universities Retirement System (SURS).</p><p><a href="https://nessie.uihr.uillinois.edu/cf/benefits/index.cfm?Item_ID=134&amp;rlink=126">403b Optional Retirement Plan</a></p><p><a href="https://nessie.uihr.uillinois.edu/cf/benefits/index.cfm?Item_ID=135&amp;rlink=134">457 Deferred Compensation Plan</a></div></div></div><div class="fusion-panel panel-default"><div class="panel-heading"><h4 class="panel-title toggle"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-481-1" data-target="#1c52423022a0ce6f6" href="#1c52423022a0ce6f6"><div class="fusion-toggle-icon-wrapper"><i class="fa-fusion-box"></i></div><div class="fusion-toggle-heading">Worker's Compensation and Injury Procedures</div></a></h4></div><div id="1c52423022a0ce6f6" class="panel-collapse collapse "><div class="panel-body toggle-content fusion-clearfix"><h3>Employee&#8217;s Responsibility</h3><ul><li>Immediately report accident/injury to supervisor either verbally or in writing</li><li>Seek medical attention or first aid immediately after the injury</li><li>Inform the medical providers that treatment is for a work-related condition</li><li>Complete and sign <a href="https://www.treasury.uillinois.edu/UserFiles/Servers/Server_338/File/riskWorkersComp/FirstReportInjuryIllness.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">First Report of Injury Form</a> within 24 hours</li><li>Cooperate with doctors and follow medical plan of treatment to achieve a complete recovery and full return to work</li></ul><h3>Supervisor&#8217;s Responsibility</h3><ul><li>Ensure that the employee receives immediate medical attention</li><li>Call for/provide transportation, if needed, and facilitate the provision of medical care as needed</li><li>Thoroughly complete the <a href="https://www.treasury.uillinois.edu/UserFiles/Servers/Server_338/File/riskWorkersComp/FirstReportInjuryIllness.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">First Report of Injury Form</a> within 24 hours and send to Human Resources</li></ul><h3>Who to Contact About Benefits and Claims</h3><p><strong>Office of Workers&#8217; Compensation and Claims Management</strong><br /> 100 Trade Centre Drive, Suite 103, MC-686, Champaign, IL 61820<br /> 217-333-1080<br /> Fax: 217-244-5152<br /> <a href="mailto:WorkComp@uillinois.edu">WorkComp@uillinois.edu</a><br /> <a href="http://www.treasury.uillinois.edu/risk_management/workers_compensation/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">treasury.uillinois.edu/risk_management/workers_compensation</a></p><p><strong>UICOMP Human Resources</strong><br /> One Illini Drive, Room A112<br /> Peoria, IL 61656<br /> 309-671-8519<br /> <a href="mailto:lkeeton@uic.edu">lkeeton@uic.edu</a></p><h3>Additional Resources</h3><p><a href="https://www.ehso.uic.edu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Environmental Health and Safety Office</a></p></div></div></div><div class="fusion-panel panel-default"><div class="panel-heading"><h4 class="panel-title toggle"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-481-1" data-target="#ff669e5c8423ec8e2" href="#ff669e5c8423ec8e2"><div class="fusion-toggle-icon-wrapper"><i class="fa-fusion-box"></i></div><div class="fusion-toggle-heading">Policies and Resources</div></a></h4></div><div id="ff669e5c8423ec8e2" class="panel-collapse collapse "><div class="panel-body toggle-content fusion-clearfix"><ul><li><a href="https://www.hr.uic.edu/policies/">University Employment Policies</a></li><li><a href="https://www.ethics.uillinois.edu/">Ethics Office</a></li><li><a href="https://www.bot.uillinois.edu/governance/general_rules">General Rules Concerning University Organization and Procedures</a></li><li><a href="https://www.hr.uillinois.edu/policy/state_federal_mandates/required_federal_and_state_posters">Required State and Federal Posters</a></li><li><a href="http://provost.uic.edu/faculty-resources/faculty-policies-procedures/">UIC Faculty Policies</a></li><li><a href="http://oae.uic.edu/">UIC Office for Access and Equity</a></li><li><a href="https://www.obfs.uillinois.edu/bfpp/">University of Illinois Business and Financial Policies and Procedures</a></li><li><a href="https://nessie.uihr.uillinois.edu/cf/policies/index.cfm?Item_id=390">University of Illinois Policy and Rules for Civil Service Staff</a></li><li><a href="https://www.bot.uillinois.edu/governance/statutes">University of Illinois Statutes</a></li></ul></div></div></div><div class="fusion-panel panel-default"><div class="panel-heading"><h4 class="panel-title toggle"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-481-1" data-target="#e36c51db32f4e1c08" href="#e36c51db32f4e1c08"><div class="fusion-toggle-icon-wrapper"><i class="fa-fusion-box"></i></div><div class="fusion-toggle-heading">Employee Performance Review</div></a></h4></div><div id="e36c51db32f4e1c08" class="panel-collapse collapse "><div class="panel-body toggle-content fusion-clearfix"><p><a href="https://www.hr.uic.edu/managing_my_performance/annual_performance_review/">Evaluation forms</a></p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="fusion-clearfix"></div></div></div><div id="deptcontactfooter" class="fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion_builder_column_1_4  fusion-one-fourth fusion-column-last 1_4"  style='margin-top:28px;margin-bottom:0px;width:25%;width:calc(25% - ( ( 4% ) * 0.25 ) );'><div class="fusion-column-wrapper" style="border-top:3px solid #ff6f59;padding: 0px 0px 0px 20px;background-position:left top;background-repeat:no-repeat;-webkit-background-size:cover;-moz-background-size:cover;-o-background-size:cover;